<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,225,1063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,882,908]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Discussion:</emphasis>
male imago of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dominguez, Molineri &amp; Mariano" authorityYear="2009" box="[528,725,882,907]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Askola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cipoensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[528,725,882,907]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Askola cipoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,828,882,908]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[733,828,882,908]" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished by the following combination of characters: 1) General coloration yellowish, abdomen washed with gray (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1122,921,947]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,194,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-63@6.[206,1381,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Askola. Figs 7–9, Askola cipoensis sp. nov., male imago. 7, general aspect, lateral view; 8, head, dorsal view; 9, head, lateral view. Figs 10–12, A. froehlichi, male imago. 10, general aspect, lateral view; 11, head, dorsal view; 12, head, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319926" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319926/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); 2) dorsal portion of eyes yellowish brown, eyes widely separated dorsally on meson of head (
<figureCitation box="[952,1065,960,986]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[206,1381,194,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-63@6.[206,1381,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Askola. Figs 7–9, Askola cipoensis sp. nov., male imago. 7, general aspect, lateral view; 8, head, dorsal view; 9, head, lateral view. Figs 10–12, A. froehlichi, male imago. 10, general aspect, lateral view; 11, head, dorsal view; 12, head, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319926" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319926/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Figs. 8–9</figureCitation>
); 3) no costal cross veins basad to bulla (
<figureCitation box="[261,352,998,1024]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,727,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-302@10.[194,1393,727,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Askola. Figs 25–27, male fore wing: 25, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.; 26, Askola paprockii sp. nov.; 27, Askola cipoensis sp. nov. Figs 28–30, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.: 28, genitalia, ventral view; 29, genitalia, lateral view; 30, penes, detail. Figs 31–33, Askola paprockii sp. nov.: 31, genitalia, ventral view; 32, genitalia, lateral view; 33, penes, detail. Figs 34–36, Askola cipoensis sp. nov.: 34, genitalia, ventral view; 35, genitalia, lateral view; 36, penes, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319934/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); 4) forceps light yellow washed with gray; 5) penes extending slightly beyond posterior margin of styliger plate (
<figureCitation box="[440,585,1037,1063]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–36" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1901,1925]" captionTargetBox="[195,1385,727,1874]" captionTargetId="figure-302@10.[194,1393,727,1877]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 25–36. Askola. Figs 25–27, male fore wing: 25, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.; 26, Askola paprockii sp. nov.; 27, Askola cipoensis sp. nov. Figs 28–30, Askola emmerichi sp.nov.: 28, genitalia, ventral view; 29, genitalia, lateral view; 30, penes, detail. Figs 31–33, Askola paprockii sp. nov.: 31, genitalia, ventral view; 32, genitalia, lateral view; 33, penes, detail. Figs 34–36, Askola cipoensis sp. nov.: 34, genitalia, ventral view; 35, genitalia, lateral view; 36, penes, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5319934" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5319934/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="34">Figs. 34–35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
